 ***NOTE: AN INTERNAL CYLINDRICAL ORIENTATION SYSTEM  ORAXI  HAS BEEN CREATED 
          FOR ALL ELEMENTS THAT WERE NOT ASSOCIATED WITH AN ORIENTATION 
          DEFINITION IN ORIGINAL AXISYMMETRIC MODEL

 ***NOTE: FOR SHELLS, MEMBRANES AND SURFACES THE PROJECTIONS OF THE LOCAL 2 AND 
          3-DIRECTIONS OF THE ORIENTATION SYSTEM  ORAXI  ONTO SURFACE OF THE 
          SHELL OR MEMBRANE ARE TAKEN AS THE LOCAL SURFACE DIRECTIONS, SO THAT 
          THE LOCAL 2-DIRECTION IS ALWAYS THE HOOP DIRECTION.

 ***WARNING: THE FRICTION MODELS IN THE ORIGINAL AXISYMMETRIC MODEL USE THE 
             SLIPTOL PARAMETER. THIS OPTION MAY RESULT IN CONVERGENCE 
             DIFFICULTIES WHEN RESULTS ARE TRANSFERRED TO THE NEW MODEL SINCE 
             Abaqus COMPUTES DIFFERENT CHARACTERISTIC ELEMENT LENGTHS IN 2D AND 
             3D MODELS. THE USE OF THE ELASTIC SLIP PARAMETER IS RECOMMENDED.

